author: cmpilato
msg: `svn revert' now cleans up reject files (see Issue #486).
not an svn_stringbuf_t *.  Removed "kind" argument (you can get it
from the entry, now), and added "name" (to do what "entry" used to
do) and *modify_flags.  Now, all mods to the entries file are
handled by this function's caller, using the data returned in *entry
and *modify_flags.  Also, .rej and .prej files are removed.
(svn_wc_revert): Pass new arguments to revert_admin_things() and
handle the cleanup of .rej and .prej files.
